[5/16/24, 8:48:28â€¯AM] Pocho: No, a VS Code solution is not the same as a coding repository. A solution is a container for one or more related projects, along with build information, Visual Studio window settings, and any miscellaneous files that aren't associated with a particular project. A coding repository, on the other hand, is a collection of files and folders that store the source code for a project.
